2235  	 	BRIGHTON - FOREIGN PAID AND C.D.S. USED AS PACKET LETTER RECEIVER; 1844 EL La Rochelle to Boston (USA) endorsed in red "Par le Steamer Caledonia ..." with La Rochelle c.d.s. & small boxed "PD" with alongside a fine red curved "FOREIGN-PAID" (Tab.M2) [overstruck by London & USA h.s.]. Brighton was one of only three ports outside London to be issued with a Foreign Paid h.s. Scarce thus. Plus pair 1843 EL St Servan to Rochester Kent and Madrid to London both with Brighton c.d.s. used on the reverse as a Packet Letter receiver, etc. (3 covers plus pictures).    	£150
